					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/sharpembrace" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(6032914); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=6032914&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610252026" alt="SharpEmbrace" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=6032914)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/sharpembrace" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(6032914); return false;" >SharpEmbrace</a></span> <span class="odate time_1584305859 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">15 Mar 2020 20:57</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4549314">
									

<p>This makes me uncomfortable but in a bad way. It's a decent pun on the jam-con theme but beyond that, it's not actually very interesting. This is just Foundation but Transformers. It's parodying the Foundation, yes, but it lacks the unique charm of the Shark Punching Centre, which a distinct personality conveyed incredibly well through its orientation document.</p>
<p>This reads like a Foundation orientation with human words replaced by Transformers alternatives. You can't say the same about the <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/10-30-a-m">SPC orientation</a>. This would be awesome if it had a unique style and persona to it but it simply doesn't.</p>
<p><strong>-1</strong></p>

							</div>

