															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/nathanoraptor13" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(3099218); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=3099218&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610252026" alt="Nathanoraptor13" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=3099218)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/nathanoraptor13" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(3099218); return false;" >Nathanoraptor13</a></span> <span class="odate time_1591721034 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">09 Jun 2020 16:43</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4682693">
									

<p>As a lifelong Transformers fan, this is obviously really fun to me; I also really like Projejct Crossover, so anything like that is aces in my book.</p>
<p>Is the memo meant to be a pre-existing character or somebody new? Given that this seems to be the Autobots' Weird Science Department, I would imagine that this is the sort of thing Wheeljack and/or Perceptor would probably be in charge of&#8230; yet the tone doesn't fit either of them.</p>
<p>And the idea of the Autobots having a version of the Foundation leads to endless possibilities - the Predacons as equivalents to the Children of the Night, Monstructor as SCP-682&#8230;</p>
<p>Another idea I really like from this is the idea that <em>every</em> planet with sapient life on it has a version of the Foundation. All worlds are just as weird as Earth.</p>
<p>What would be really fun - if DrScaramouche was willing to write a &quot;sequel&quot; - is to see what the <em>Decepticons</em> make of the various anomalies on Cybertron? Do they have an equivalent unit to this, possibly led by Shockwave?</p>
<p>+1</p>

							</div>

								
					
